<h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2 leading-tight">Triple-Triple Words</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8 not-prose">Anagram · 2-letter words</p>

    <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
      <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
      <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
      <span>7 min read</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">In Scrabble, a triple-triple is the holy grail of scoring. When your word spans two Triple Word Score squares in a single play, the multipliers stack: 3 × 3 = 9. A modest 20-point word becomes 180 points. Add the 50-point bingo bonus and you're looking at 230+ points from a single turn.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">How the 9x Multiplier Works</h2>

    <p>The Scrabble rules are clear: when a word covers multiple premium squares, word multipliers are applied sequentially. Two TWS squares means the word value is tripled, then tripled again.</p>

    <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Scoring Formula</p>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Base word value × 3 (first TWS) × 3 (second TWS) + 50 (bingo bonus if all 7 tiles used) = <span class="text-white font-medium">Final score</span></p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mt-2">Example: RETAILS (base 7) × 9 = 63 + 50 bingo = 113 points</p>
    </div>

    <p>Any Double Letter Score (DLS) or Triple Letter Score (TLS) squares the word passes through are calculated first, before word multipliers apply. A high-value tile on a TLS within a triple-triple produces astronomical scores.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Where Triple-Triples Are Possible</h2>

